#: src/Admin/WebhooksAdminPage.php:144
msgid "Delivery:"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/WebhooksAdminPage.php:145
msgid "When a subscribed event fires (e.g. points awarded, badge earned), the dispatcher POSTs a JSON body to your endpoint URL. Delivery is async (Action Scheduler queue) so the page-load that triggered the event is never blocked."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/WebhooksAdminPage.php:148
msgid "Signature verification:"
msgstr ""

#. translators: %s: header name wrapped in code
#: src/Admin/WebhooksAdminPage.php:153
#, php-format
msgid "Each request includes a %s header containing an HMAC-SHA256 signature of the raw body, computed with your webhook secret. Always verify before trusting the delivery - anyone can hit your URL."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/WebhooksAdminPage.php:161
msgid "Retry behavior:"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/WebhooksAdminPage.php:162
msgid "A non-2xx response (or a network failure) schedules a retry with exponential backoff (1m → 5m → 30m). After 3 failed attempts the webhook is automatically paused. Resume by editing the row in the database (set is_active=1) - admin UI flag in v1.1."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/WebhooksAdminPage.php:165
msgid "Payload shape:"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/WebhooksAdminPage.php:166
msgid "JSON object with `event` (e.g. badge_earned), `user_id`, `data` (event-specific fields), and `fired_at` (ISO 8601). Match against the event slug to dispatch on the receiver side."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/WebhooksAdminPage.php:170
msgid "Use HTTPS endpoints only. Rotate the secret if you suspect a leak (delete + recreate the webhook). Failed deliveries log to the WP error log with full request/response context."
msgstr ""

